'''Anis Hadj Moussa''' (born 11 February 2002) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Eredivisie]] club [[Feyenoord]]. Born in France, he represents the [[Algeria national football team|Algeria national team]].

== Club career ==
Born in [[Paris]], Anis Hadj Moussa first played for [[US Torcy]] and FC Montfermeil, before joining the [[RC Lens]] academy in 2018.<ref name="panamefoot">{{Cite web |date=2020-10-15 |title=3 joueurs Franciliens passés par le FC Montfermeil dont un du PSG appelés en équipe nationale Algérienne U20 pour disputer les éliminatoires de la CAN… |url=https://www.panamefoot.fr/3-joueurs-franciliens-passes-par-le-fc-montfermeil-dont-un-du-psg-appeles-en-equipe-nationale-algerienne-u20-pour-disputer-les-eliminatoires-de-la-can/ |access-date=2024-03-17 |website=Panamefoot |language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Anis Hadj Moussa |url=https://rclens5962.footeo.com/saison-2021-2022/national-2/equipe-rc-lens-n2/joueur-anis-hadj-moussa-4.html |access-date=2024-03-17 |website=RC Lens |language=fr |via=Footeo}}</ref>

He first played with Lens' reserve in [[Championnat National 2|National 2]],<ref name=lensois/> before signing his first senior contract in Belgium with [[Olympic Charleroi]] in the summer of 2022.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Maljean |first1=Vincent |last2=Delforge |first2=Jérémy |date=2024-03-16 |title=Anis Hadj Moussa, le gros coup des Dogues |url=https://www.lavenir.net/regions/charleroi/sports/2022/07/29/anis-hadj-moussa-le-gros-coup-des-dogues-EXBKCJM5IRBHXIEGEI5XSZ6SR4/ |access-date=2024-03-17 |website=[[L'Avenir (Belgian newspaper)|L'Avenir]] |language=fr}}</ref><ref name="sudinfo">{{Cite web |date=2022-07-29 |title=L'Olympic (N1) recrute un international algérien U23 du RC Lens: "Une aubaine!" |url=https://www.sudinfo.be/art/974908/article/2022-07-29/lolympic-n1-recrute-un-international-algerien-u23-du-rc-lens-une-aubaine |access-date=2024-03-17 |website={{ill|Sudinfo|fr|Groupe Sudmedia}} |language=fr}}</ref> There he soon became a standout in the [[Belgian National Division 1|Nationale 1]].<ref name=lensois/><ref name="dhnet"/>

In June 2023, Hadj Moussa switched to [[K. Patro Eisden Maasmechelen|Patro Eisden Maasmechelen]], which had just achieved promotion to [[Challenger Pro League]] the previous season.<ref name=lensois/><ref name="dhnet">{{Cite web |date=2024-03-16 |title=Anis Hadj-Moussa quitte l'Olympic pour la D1B |url=https://www.dhnet.be/sports/sport-regional/charleroi/2023/06/09/anis-hadj-moussa-quitte-lolympic-pour-la-d1b-TAPGLCR3YNA7ZHNXEXBQIOTELQ/ |access-date=2024-03-17 |website=[[La Dernière Heure]] |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-06-09 |title=N1 {{!}}L'Olympic de Charleroi perd un grand talent: Anis Hadj-Moussa rejoint le Patro Eisden Maasmechelen en D1B |url=https://www.sudinfo.be/id674855/article/2023-06-09/n1-lolympic-de-charleroi-perd-un-grand-talent-anis-hadj-moussa-rejoint-le-patro |access-date=2024-03-17 |website=Sudinfo |language=fr}}</ref>

In February 2024, he was loaned to [[SBV Vitesse|Vitesse Arnhem]] in the [[Eredivisie]], with a buyout clause.<ref name="lensois">{{Cite web |last=De Mester |first=Eloise |date=2024-02-06 |title=Formé à Lens, Anis Hadj-Moussa s'engage avec le Vitesse Arnhem |url=https://www.lensois.com/forme-a-lens-anis-hadj-moussa-sengage-avec-le-vitesse-arnhem/ |access-date=2024-03-17 |website=Lensois.com |language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=February 1, 2024 |title=Anis Hadj-moussa (21) van Patro Eisden naar Vitesse |url=https://www.vitesse.nl/nieuws/2024/anis-hadj-moussa-21-van-patro-eisden-naar-vitesse |access-date=17 March 2024 |website=[[SBV Vitesse|Vitesse]]}}</ref> Despite joining a struggling side,<ref name=lensois/> he soon managed to stand out with the [[Arnhem]] club.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Benamrouche |first=Sofiane |date=2024-03-13 |title=Pays-Bas : d'anciens internationaux néerlandais font les éloges de Anis Hadj Moussa |url=https://lagazettedufennec.com/pays-bas-danciens-internationaux-neerlandais-font-les-eloges-de-anis-hadj-moussa/ |access-date=2024-03-17 |website=La Gazette du Fennec |language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref name="DZ">{{Cite web |last=Bousksou |first=Manel |date=2024-03-13 |title=Pays-Bas : Hadj Moussa supervisé par le PSV Eindhoven |url=https://www.dzfoot.com/verts-deurope/pays-bas-anis-hadj-moussa-supervise-par-le-psv-eindhoven-256118.html |access-date=2024-03-17 |website=DZFOOT |language=fr-FR}}</ref>

In April 2024, Dutch club [[Feyenoord]] announced that Moussa would join them for the 2024–25 season on a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2515281-feyenoord-legt-vitesse-smaakmaker-hadj-moussa-vast-voor-meerdere-seizoenen |title=Feyenoord legt Vitesse-smaakmaker Hadj Moussa vast voor meerdere seizoenen |trans-title=Feyenoord signs Vitesse star Hadj Moussa for multiple seasons |language=Dutch |date=3 April 2024 |access-date=3 April 2024}}</ref> With the move, Moussa earned his previous club Patro Eisden a record transfer fee.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/patro-eisden-jubelt-feyenoord-deal-hadj-moussa-hoogtepunt-in-onze-historie |title=Patro Eisden jubelt: 'Feyenoord-deal Hadj-Moussa hoogtepunt in onze historie' |trans-title=Patro Eisden celebrate: 'Feyenoord-deal Hadj-Moussa new highlight in our history' |language=nl |date=3 April 2024 |access-date=3 April 2024}}</ref> On 6 November 2024, he scored his first [[UEFA Champions League]] goal in a 1-3 home loss against [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]].<ref>{{cite web |title='Lichtpuntje' Feyenoord zorgt voor discussie: 'Dit is wel profvoetbal...' |url=https://www.voetbalprimeur.nl/nieuws/1236894/hadj-moussa-kan-ondanks-goal-niet-overtuigen-dit-is-wel-profvoetbal.html |date=6 November 2024 |access-date=27 November 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
Anis Hadj Moussa is a youth international for Algeria, having played with the [[Algeria national under-20 football team|under-20]]<ref name="panamefoot" /><ref name="lensois" /> and [[Algeria national under-23 football team|under-23]].<ref name="sudinfo"/><ref name="DZ"/>

Hadj Moussa made his debut for the senior [[Algeria national football team|Algeria national team]] on 22 March 2024 in a [[Exhibition game|friendly]] against [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/698288/bolivia-algeria|title=Algeria v Bolivia game report|date=22 March 2024}}</ref> He scored his first goal for Algeria on 3 June 2026 during the 1–0 friendly victory against the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]].

